How to get your Access Key ID and Secret Access Key:
‚¶Å	Login to the AWS Console: https://console.aws.amazon.com/
‚¶Å	On the top right, click your username, then choose "Security credentials".
‚¶Å	Scroll to the section called "Access keys".
‚¶Å	Click "Create access key" and Select "Command Line Interface (CLI)"
You'll see: "Access Key ID" & "Secret Access Key", Copy and store these securely


How to download and install AWS CLI:
‚¶Å	Download the AWS CLI installer: curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -Lo "aws-cli.zip"
‚¶Å	Unzip the installer: unzip aws-cli.zip -d aws-cli
‚¶Å	Install AWS CLI: sudo ./aws-cli/aws/install
‚¶Å	Verify installation: aws --version


How to download and install AWS SAM:
‚¶Å	Install dependencies: sudo apt install -y curl unzip zip python3 python3-pip docker.io
‚¶Å	Download the AWS SAM installer: curl -Lo aws-sam.zip https://github.com/aws/aws-sam-cli/releases/download/v1.142.1/aws-sam-cli-linux-x86_64.zip
‚¶Å	Unzip the installer: unzip aws-sam.zip -d aws-sam
‚¶Å	Install the package: sudo ./aws-sam/install
‚¶Å	Verify installation: sam --version


How to configure AWS CLI with your IAM credentials:
‚¶Å	Verify the aws cli is installed: aws --version
‚¶Å	Configure AWS CLI with IAM: aws configure
‚¶Å	It will prompt for:
‚¶Å	AWS Access Key ID: üîë (from IAM user)
‚¶Å	AWS Secret Access Key: üîí (from IAM user)
‚¶Å	Default region name: e.g., us-east-1
‚¶Å	Default output format: json (or yaml, text, etc.)
‚¶Å	Verify your Configuration: aws configure list
‚¶Å	Test Access (STS = Security Token Service): aws sts get-caller-identity
